reviews.text: Holy yum. Omg. Literally DELICIOUS!  I will be bringing everybody I know here. 1000% worth the price and your tastebuds will thank you. Seriously some of the best food I‚Äôve had while eating out. I said mmmm or yum every single bite. üî•üî•

I've had this craving for Middle Eastern food for the past week and Damascus Kitchen did not disappoint!

I ordered a Damascus Chicken - generous helping of chicken and that soft pita! It came nicely wrapped in a folded paper plate so you could open it up and hold the sandwich better when eating it.

My husband got a lamb wrap. He loves it!! It looks great too, and the sandwich is grilled on the outside.

We also ordered a portion of chicken plate to-go for the next day.

The owners are generous; we were still tucking into our food when the lady owner came to our table with a plate of freshly-cooked falafel! *drools*

And later, the gentleman owner poured us little cups of hot tea. My lucky day, praise to God!

If you're ever at Fork Forty, and you cannot decide what to have, either of the above will not disappoint you.

My only regret was not packing away some baklavas. But hey, I will be back! üòä

I scored. Looked up Greek food as I was driving through Salem. Excellent meal, great services, huge portions. Shared with my husband and we still had leftovers. Asked for extra sauce and she gave me a nice large portion. Very friendly probably husband/wife team. We drive through a lot and this will be my place

We travelled from Vancouver to Salem yesterday to try Damascus Kitchen. It surpassed my expectations, and I was thrilled with the authentic food and the original taste of everything. The cleanliness, the taste, the service, the atmosphere, the coziness of the place, all were 10/10. I recommend give them a try. They have just started two months ago. This is an amazing start up.

I had a truly great experience here. I came in alone and was immediately welcomed with kindness and genuine hospitality. The people working here were so friendly and respectful ‚Äî it honestly made the whole visit feel special.

I ordered a shawarma, and it was absolutely delicious ‚Äî full of rich flavor, perfectly seasoned, and made with real care. You can tell they put pride into their food, and it really shows in the taste.

It‚Äôs rare to find a place where both the food and the people are this good. I‚Äôll definitely be coming back and highly recommend it to anyone looking for a quality meal and warm service.
